RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 12500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MAY 5 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Lesser Claiming Races For $6,000(AB $8,000) Or Less Not Consid ered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAKE CHARGE GWEN unhurried early, took closer order nearing the far turn, fanned four wide in the last turn, and prevailed after a multi-horse scramble to the wire. BABS DELIGHT chased from the rail, angled out at the top of the stretch bumping into PRANCE and rallied from the rail and just missed. THRILL OF THE NITE broke sharply then set a pressured pace, was unable to move on with NO BAKK TALK into the far turn, angled in when roused at the head of the lane then bumped into an inside foe, and was bested. NO BAKK TALK pressed the early pace, inherited the lead into the far turn, was showing signs of tiring into the stretch, and was steadied in the final strides. PRANCE trailed early, gained closer order then was sandwiched and checked hard in traffic. CAPA BELLA chased outside and failed to threaten. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the stretch run. After review BABS DELIGHT was disqualified and placed fourth for interference to PRANCE. THRILL OF THE NITE was disqualified and placed fifth for interference to PRANCE.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Thrill of the Nite
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke sharply, angled in, bumped, bested

FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $25,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $3 1,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISSCZECH quickly took command, drew clear to good margins nearing the final turn, and was ridden out to an easy victory in record time. SINGING BELL stalked inside, and chased into the stretch but was no match for the winner. BEAUTIFUL MESS trailed the field, closed well late to earn show honors. MI REYNA stalked from the three path, and lacked a kick that was needed. DAMN THE TORPEDOES fanned four wide into the opening turn, and was through early.

ENTRY.NAME: Missczech
ENTRY.COMMENT: took command, drew clear, ridden out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alberta Fall Classic Distaff H. CENTURY DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 86. Stakes Purse 50000. A STAKE FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD ALBERTA BREDS FILLY AND MARES. $100 fee to accompany the nomination. A payment of $600 is required to pass the entry box and a fee of $300 to start. After a payment of 2% to all owners finishing 6th to last, 60% of the purse to be paid to the winner, 20% to second, 10% to third, 6% to fourth and 4% to fifth. Preference into the race to be determined by earnings on the date of entry. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. The fiel d will be limited to 12 starters. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANCE SHOES was reserved off the early lead under a snug hold, moved up between foes in the backstretch to contest the pace, took over willingly in the far turn, and kicked away when asked. PLUM BLUE saved ground inside, was asked to quicken leaving the backstretch, was roused at the head of the lane then rallied inside of JELLI and edged clear for second. JELLI was under a strong hold early when passing by the frontside, pressed three wide through the backstretch, was unable to move on with the eventual winner, rallied outside of PLUM BLUE then missed finishing clearly third-best. SASSY CINDERELLA sat off the early pace, and lacked a bid. GRACEFUL SPIRIT quickly went to the front to set the pace, and tired early.

ENTRY.NAME: Jelli
ENTRY.COMMENT: strong hold, pressed 3w, rallied outside, missed

SAWCHUK settled mid-pack, swung five in the final turn, and was just up late to score show honors. SUDDENLY FAMOUS saved early, chased into the final turn, and was nipped at the wire. CAPE'S LEGACY chased to no avail. JAKOBS ROCKET BOY contested the early pace, and faded steadily. HOLY JOE trailed throughout.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKTILLYOUDROP went four to five wide leaving the opening turn, moved up alongside RAILWAY to challenge the lead, responded to pressure from DECOY and prevailed under a drive. DECOY was under a snug hold leaving the opening turn, moved up closer then launched an all-out bid into the stretch but was unable to get by after a determined effort. CREDIBILITY raced wide through the opening turn, fanned three wide entering the backstretch, was unable to move on with foes then was kept to steady handling through the stretch and held. COUNTRIFIED trailed early, shifted out to the three path, and improved position late. VIATURE steadied leaving the opening turn, gained closer order, and weakened. EL NOBLE checked then angled out sharply leaving the opening turn, trailed and lacked a serious bid. DRINKING AGAIN showed some early speed into the first turn, and dropped back. RAILWAY sprinted to the lead, was overtaken and gaveway. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry in the first turn but made no change.

ENTRY.NAME: Decoy
ENTRY.COMMENT: snug hold, all out bid, needed more

FLASHFORDANI raced three-wide early, gave chased leaving the backstretch, rallied four wide into the stretch, and inched clear for place. ZICATELA raced four to five wide leaving the backstretch, sat in a striking range from the four path, rallied in the stretch, and weakened in the final yards. ESCROW STYLE unhurried early, chased hard leaving the backstretch, and flattened out. THESHACK was under a snug hold inside early, stalked the pacesetters in the backstretch, and evened out. SILVERFOOT bid belatedly. PUMP THE BRAKES contended the early pace, dueled through the backstretch, was unable to move on with rival, and gave way.
